@startuml logical-architecture-its-detail
!include ../_shared/its-uml-style.puml

title Issue Tracking System - Logical Architecture Detail

top to bottom direction

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 34
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam rectangle {
  FontSize 12
  BorderColor #37474F
  FontColor #263238
}

rectangle "Presentation Layer\n--\nMain launches JavaFXApp\nJavaFXApp initializes ApplicationContext\n\nUI code should call controllers only;\ncontrollers/services/repositories are reused by any UI toolkit." as PRES <<presentation>> #E3F2FD

rectangle "Composition Root\n--\nApplicationContext\n  exposes controller set for UI\n\nApplicationBootstrap\n  initializes DB schema/seed\n  creates JDBC repositories\n  creates services, policies, controllers\n\nShared runtime objects\n  PermissionPolicy\n  SystemClock\n  PasswordHasher\n  SessionStore\n  CommentIdGenerator" as BOOT <<bootstrap>> #E8F5E9

rectangle "Controller Layer\n--\nAuthenticationController\n  login(), logout()\n\nDashboardController\n  viewProjects(), viewUsers()\n\nProjectController\n  viewProjectAdminDetail(), viewProjectNonAdminDetail()\n  viewProjectParticipants()\n  create/rename/changeDescription/delete project\n  add/remove participant\n\nIssueController\n  register/search/view/update issue\n  comments, dependencies, priority\n  available actions for UI\n\nAssignmentController\n  start assignment, assign, reassign, change verifier\n\nIssueStateController\n  changeStatus()\n\nDeletedIssueController\n  view, soft-delete, restore, purge overflow, purge one\n\nAccountController / StatisticsController" as CTRL <<controller>> #FFF8E1

rectangle "Service / Policy Layer\n--\nAuthenticationService / AccountService\nDashboardSummaryService\nProjectService\nIssueService\nIssueWorkflowService\nAssignmentService\nAssignmentRecommendationService + KNN engine\nIssueStateService\nDeletedIssueService\nStatisticsService\nPermissionPolicy\n\nServices coordinate permissions, project membership,\nrepository lookups, domain behavior, and result DTOs." as SERVICE <<service>> #FFF3E0

rectangle "Domain Model\n--\nUser, Project, ProjectMember\nIssue, Comment, IssueHistory, IssueDependency\n\nDomain value categories\nRole, IssueStatus, Priority\nCommentPurpose, ActionType\n\nDomain objects hold issue workflow state,\nassignment history, comments, dependencies,\nand project/user concepts." as DOMAIN <<domain>> #F1F8E9

rectangle "Application Ports\n--\nRepository interfaces\n  UserRepository, ProjectRepository, IssueRepository\n  CommentRepository, IssueHistoryRepository\n  IssueDependencyRepository\n  AssignmentRecommendationRepository\n  DeletedIssueRepository\n  DashboardSummaryRepository\n  StatisticsRepository\n\nTechnical ports used by services\n  Clock\n  PasswordHashing\n  CurrentUserSession\n  CommentIdProvider" as PORTS <<port>> #E0F2F1

rectangle "Infrastructure Adapters\n--\nJDBC adapters\n  JdbcUserRepository, JdbcProjectRepository, JdbcIssueRepository\n  JdbcCommentRepository, JdbcIssueHistoryRepository\n  JdbcIssueDependencyRepository\n  JdbcAssignmentRecommendationRepository\n  JdbcDeletedIssueRepository\n  JdbcDashboardSummaryRepository\n  JdbcStatisticsRepository\n  JdbcRepositoryFactory\n\nJDBC helpers\n  JdbcIssueQueries, JdbcIssueRowMapper, JdbcIssueWriteSupport\n\nTechnical adapters\n  PasswordHasher, SessionStore, SystemClock, CommentIdGenerator" as INFRA <<adapter>> #F3E5F5

database "Oracle Database\n--\nusers / projects / project_members\nissues / comments / issue_history\nissue_dependencies / credentials" as DB #ECEFF1

PRES -down-> BOOT : starts and requests context
BOOT -down-> CTRL : constructs controllers
BOOT -down-> SERVICE : constructs services
BOOT -down-> INFRA : constructs adapters
CTRL -down-> SERVICE : calls use-case services
SERVICE -down-> DOMAIN : changes domain objects
SERVICE -down-> PORTS : uses repositories and ports
INFRA -up-> PORTS : implements repository / technical ports
INFRA -down-> DB : SQL read/write

legend bottom
  - This is a logical architecture view, not a complete class diagram.
  - Repository interfaces and small service ports are treated as application ports.
  - Infrastructure depends on ports; services do not directly create JDBC/session/hash implementations.
  - Current main code has a JavaFX entry point. Additional UI toolkits should reuse ApplicationContext and controllers.
endlegend
@enduml
